         <div n="1">
            <pb n="1"/>
            <head rend="center">
               <hi rend="superscript">RECOMMENDATIONS OF THE PRELIMINARY COMMITTEE APPPOINTED</hi><lb/>
               <hi rend="superscript">BY THE INTERNATIONAL CONGRESS AT THE HAGUE OF 9TH</hi><lb/>
               <hi rend="superscript">AUGUST, 1907, TO PROPOSE ARRANGEMENTS FOR ORGANISING</hi><lb/>
               <hi rend="superscript">THE SUBJECT RACES JOINT COMMITTEE ON A PERMANENT AND</hi><lb/>
               <hi rend="superscript">EFFECTIVE INTERNATIONAL BASIS</hi><lb/>   
            </head>
            <p n="1"> <!-- amaze mosafiqrebelia -->
               <list rend="numbered">
                  <item n="1">That this Committee be called The International<lb/>
                     Subject Races Committee.</item>
                  <item n="2">THAT the purpose of the Committee shall be to pro-<lb/>
                     vide opportunities for cooperation between the<lb/>
                     promoters and supporters of organisations favour-<lb/>
                     able to the protection of the rights, and advance-<lb/>
                     ment of the interests, of subject races and nation-<lb/>
                     alities, whaterver their grade of civilisation.</item>
                  <item n="3">THAT its intention being to assist the organisations<lb/>
                     represented on it in securing unity and harmony of <lb/>
                     action without in any way hampering their indepen-<lb/>
                     dence, the Committee shal neither usurp the func-<lb/>
                     tions nor interfere in the management of those<lb/>
                     organisations nor be responsible for any action they<lb/>
                     may take on their own responsibility.</item>
                  <item n="4">That in advocating the cause of any subject nation-<lb/>
                     ality the Committee shall maintain a strict neutral-<lb/>
                     ity between any sections into which the national<lb/>
                     party may be divided.</item>
               </list>
               <pb n="2"/>
               <list rend="numbered">
                  <item n="5">THAT the head-quarters of the Joint Committee<lb/>
                     shall, at present, be in London, and its duties<lb/>
                     shall include: -<lb/>
                     (a) Such efforts as it can make towards the for-<lb/>
                     mation of allied Commitees, in other centres.<lb/>
                     (b) Such assistance as it can give in arousing<lb/>
                     public interest in the objects aimed at and<lb/>
                     the work done by any or all of the organisa-<lb/>
                     tions associated with it and by communcations<lb/>
                     to the Press, by meetings and lectures, and by<lb/>
                     other methods which members may suggest and<lb/>
                     the Committee approve.<lb/>
                     (c) The arrangement, if possible, of an Interna-<lb/>
                     tional Congress in each year, generally in one<lb/>
                     of the European capitals, at which delegates<lb/>
                     from the different countreis may confer with<lb/>
                     one another, and agree to take common action.<lb/>
                  </item>
                  <item n="6">THAT allied Committees being left to arrange their<lb/> 
                     own details of organisations, the Central Committee<lb/>
                     shall be composed of delegates from the several<lb/>
                     organisations represented upon it, not more than<lb/>
                     three delegates being appointed by each organisa-<lb/>
                     tion, and the Committee shall have power to co-opt<lb/>
                     in certain cases, individuals not members of the<lb/>
                     organisations represented. Such co-opted members<lb/>
                     not to exceed one-fourth of the Committee at the<lb/>
                     time of co-optation.
                  </item>
               </list>
               <pb n="3"/>
               <list rend="numbered">
                  <item n="7">THAT the Joint Committee may appoint an Executive<lb/>
                     or Sub-Committees, and <add place="above">shall</add> elect for its first year,<lb/>
                     a Chairman, an Honorary Secretary, and a Treasurer,<lb/>
                     or other officers.</item>
                  <item n="8">THAT each organisation represented on the Joint<lb/>
                     Committee shall contribute not less than Â£2. per<lb/>
                     annum owards its funds, the amounts being due at<lb/>
                     the time of joining and annually afterwards from<lb/>
                     that date; and that general subscribers of 10s.<lb/>
                     or upwards, shall be entitled to copies of all its<lb/>
                     publications and to the right of entrance to its<lb/>
                     International Congresses or other publich gatherings,<lb/>
                     but not of voting.</item>
               </list>
            </p>
